  "text": "Our results are consistent with previous findings by Cederholm [CITATION_1] and Weber [CITATION_2] . Cederholm found no difference in duration of sensory block during epidural analgesia with 20 mL ropivacaine 0.5 % or 0.75 % either with or without epinephrine 5 μg/mL. Weber did not find an effect of epinephrine 5 μg/mL added to 20 mL ropivacaine 0.5 % and 0.2 % on postoperative analgesia via a femoral catheter after total knee replacement.",
